    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Another employment agency\ncomplaint is registered today by\nCharles Klat and J. H. Sloane,\nbridge carpenters. They were sent\nby Lyons employment Office, 405\nFront av., tot Vulcan, supposedly\ngoing to 60 to work for Bates &\nRogers on the Columbia river.\nWhen they arrived there they were\ntold that no men were wanted and\nstatement written to that effect\non the backs of the employment\nOffice blanks.\n\n\nThe trip cost the two men $40\napiece and they found on returning\nthat the employment Office Is still\nadvertising for bridge engineers.\nWhile they expected to get back\nthe fee they had paid the agent\nthey are out all their expenses."
    }
  ]
